Stock Market Trend Tracker



In a stock market analysis system, a sequence of stock prices is recorded over time. Analysts want to identify the longest increasing trend in the stock prices.

A subsequence is formed by deleting some or no elements from the original sequence without changing the order of the remaining elements.

Your task is to determine the length of the longest increasing subsequence of stock prices.

Input format :
First line contains an integer n — the number of stock prices
Second line contains n space-separated integers representing the stock prices array prices[]
Output format :
Print the result in the format:
Length of Longest Increasing Subsequence: X
Where X is the length of the longest increasing subsequence.
Code constraints :
The length of prices is between 1 and 2500.

Each price is between 1 and 10^5.

Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
5
10 9 2 5 3
Output 1 :
Length of Longest Increasing Subsequence: 2
Input 2 :
3
6 7 9
Output 2 :
Length of Longest Increasing Subsequence: 3

Solution:

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;



int main(){
    
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    
    vector<int>nums(n);
    
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
    {
        cin>>nums[i];
    }
    
    int left = 0;
    int max_len = 0;
    
    for(int right = 1;right < n; right++){
        
        if(nums[right-1] > nums[right]){
            
            left = right;
        }
        
        max_len = max(max_len,right-left+1);
        
        
    }
    
    cout<<max_len;
    
    
}
